<item>
            <title>[LU-18871] &quot;which: no ofed_info in ...&quot; message from lustre-client-dkms causes frequent confusion</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-18871</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&quot;which: no ofed_info in ...&quot; message from lustre-client-dkms causes frequent confusion&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The construct is seen in a few places and leaks via stderr when ofed_info does not exist.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;if which ofed_info &amp;gt;/dev/null ; then
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This causes confusion among users that are not using MOFED.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This can be quashed by adding the redirect of stderr to /dev/null or using `command -v` to get the same effect.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
